# The c() function "combines" a list into a single object. x <- c( 30, 27, 31, 28 )
sum <- sum( x ) length <- length( x ) mean <- sum / length
message( "Mean:" ) print( mean )

x <- c( 30, 27, 31, 28 )
message( "Mean:" ) print( mean( x ) )

x <- c( 30, 27, 31, 28 ) distanceFromMean <- x - mean( x ) distanceFromMeanSquared <- distanceFromMean ** 2 distanceFromMeanSquaredSum <- sum( distanceFromMeanSquared ) variance <- distanceFromMeanSquaredSum / ( length( x ) - 1 ) standardDeviation <- sqrt( variance )
message( "Standard deviation:" ) print( standardDeviation )
